#let circ = $circle.stroked.tiny$

Let $X$ be the point on the side $A B$ of the triangle $A B C$ such that
$frac(B X, X A) = 9$. Let $M$ be the midpoint of $B X$ and let $Y$ be the point
on $B C$ such that $angle B M Y = 90^circ$. Suppose $A C$ has length 20 and
that the area of the triangle $X Y C$ is $frac{9, 100)$ of the area of the
triangle $A B C$. Find the length of $B C$.
